# [[may well]], [[well might]] (+ infinitive); [[whatever]], [[no matter what]] (even though) someone [[do]]es/[[say]]s, etc.
#: {{uxi|fr|on '''a beau''' faire|t='''whatever''' you do; '''no matter''' what one does}}
#: {{uxi|fr|on '''a beau''' protester|t='''however much''' you protest}}
#: {{uxi|fr|il a ''' eu beau''' essayer|t=try as he '''might'''}}
#: {{ux|fr|On '''a beau''' rappeler, personne ne répond.|t=You can call back '''as much as you like'''/'''However much''' you call back/'''Even if''' you call back, nobody answers.}}
#: {{uxi|fr|On '''a beau''' dire, il n'est pas bête.|t=Say '''what you like''', he's not stupid.}}
#* {{quote-text|fr|year=1921|author=w:Marcel Proust|title=Le Côté Guermantes|section=II
|passage=« Cette pierre vivante '''a beau''' être mon cousin, elle me fair peur {{...}} »
|translation=''This living stone may well be my cousin, but it frightens me.''}}
#* {{quote-song
|fr
|title=Le Prochain Amour
|lyricist=Jacques Brel
|album=Marieke
|year=1961
|passage=On '''a beau''' faire '''on a beau''' dire / Ça fait du bien d'être amoureux / Je sais je sais que ce prochain amour / Sera pour moi la prochaine défaite
|translation=Do '''whatever you like,''' say '''however much you want''' / that it feels good to be in love; / I know, I know that this next love / will be my next defeat.}}

====Usage notes====
Followed by an infinitive expressing the verb "do", "say", etc.
